ated by setting)\\n\\n3. **Important**: This hook does **NOT push shadow branches** to remote. Shadow branches remain local only.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **4. PREPARECOMMITMSG HOOK (When User Commits)**\\n\\n**File**: `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/4/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` (lines 295-400)\\n\\n#### When this runs:\\n- Triggered by git `prepare-commit-msg` hook before user edits commit message\\n\\n#### What it does:\\n\\n1. **Adds checkpoint ID trailer**:\\n   - Generates a random 12-hex-char checkpoint ID\\n   - Appends `Entire-Checkpoint: <id>` trailer to commit message\\n   - User can remove this before committing to skip linking\\n\\n2. **Does NOT save or push anything** - just adds metadata to the message\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **5. SHADOW BRANCHES (Never Pushed)**\\n\\nShadow branches store provisional checkpoint data during a session:\\n- **Format**: `entire/<base-commit-hash[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>`\\n- **Contents**: Session metadata directory with:\\n  - `full.jsonl` - session transcript (updated during turn)\\n  - `prompt.txt` - user prompts (built during turn)\\n  - `tasks/<tool-use-id>/` - task checkpoints (if applicable)\\n- **Lifetime**: Created on first SaveStep, carried forward through commits, deleted after PostCommit condenses\\n- **Persistence**: Exists only locally; **never pushed to remote**\\n- **Purpose**: Holds session data until PostCommit condenses it to `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **6. METADATA BRANCH** (`entire/checkpoints/v1`)\\n\\nThis is the permanent checkpoint storage, pushed to remote:\\n- **Created**: By `PostCommit` via `CondenseSession()` → `store.WriteCommitted()`\\n- **Format**: Sharded tree: `<checkpoint_id[:2]>/<checkpoint_id[2:]>/`\\n- **Contents** (per checkpoint):\\n  ```\\n  metadata.json          # CheckpointSummary (aggregated stats, session IDs, timestamps)\\n  full.jsonl             # Session transcript\\n  prompt.txt             # Session prompts\\n  content_hash.txt       # SHA256 