e Addition\\n\\nAdd a new field to `session.State`:\\n\\n```go\\n// PushedDuringTurnRemote is set by PrePush when checkpoints are pushed\\n// while the session is ACTIVE with TurnCheckpointIDs. Stores the remote\\n// name so turn-end can push the finalized transcript to the same remote.\\n// Empty string means no push happened during this turn.\\nPushedDuringTurnRemote string `json:\\\"pushed_during_turn_remote,omitempty\\\"`\\n```\\n\\n### PrePush Changes\\n\\nAfter successfully pushing `entire/checkpoints/v1`, iterate all ACTIVE sessions that have non-empty `TurnCheckpointIDs` and set `PushedDuringTurnRemote = remote` on each.\\n\\nThis records: \\\"your provisional checkpoint is now visible remotely — when you finalize it, push the update.\\\"\\n\\n### HandleTurnEnd Changes\\n\\nAfter `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints` succeeds:\\n\\n1. Check if `PushedDuringTurnRemote` is non-empty\\n2. Verify `push_sessions` setting is not disabled (belt and suspenders)\\n3. Print `[entire] Pushing finalized checkpoint transcripts to <remote>...` to stderr\\n4. Call `pushBranchIfNeeded(ctx, remote, paths.MetadataBranchName)`\\n5. Push trails branch if applicable\\n6. Clear `PushedDuringTurnRemote`\\n\\n### InitializeSession Changes\\n\\nClear `PushedDuringTurnRemote` on new turn start (alongside existing `TurnCheckpointIDs` clearing).\\n\\n### Proposed Flow (After)\\n\\n```\\nTurnStart → ACTIVE\\nAgent makes changes\\nAgent commits → PostCommit condenses to entire/checkpoints/v1 (local)\\nAgent pushes  → PrePush pushes entire/checkpoints/v1 (remote has provisional)\\n             → PrePush sets PushedDuringTurnRemote on ACTIVE sessions with TurnCheckpointIDs\\nAgent continues working...\\nTurnEnd → IDLE\\n  └─ SaveStep writes trailing conversation to shadow branch\\n  └─ HandleTurnEnd finalizes transcript on entire/checkpoints/v1 (local)\\n  └─ HandleTurnEnd sees PushedDuringTurnRemote, pushes entire/checkpoints/v1 ← NEW\\n  └─ Remote now has finalized transcript ✓\\n```\\n\\n## Multi-Session Scenarios\\n\\n### Scenario 1: IDLE + two ACTIVE sessions\\n\\n- IDLE session A contributed a checkpoint on a prior turn\\n- ACTIVE session B is doing research (no commits)\\n- ACTIVE session C commits and pushes → A+C checkpoints pushed\\n  - PrePush sets `PushedDuringTurnRemote` on C (ACTIVE with TurnCheckpointIDs)\\n  - B has no TurnCheckpointIDs, so not flagged\\n- C ends turn → finalizes C's transcript → pushes → remote up to date\\n\\n### Scenario 2: Two ACTIVE sessions both committing\\n\\n- A commits → A.TurnCheckpointIDs = [cpA]\\n- B commits → B.TurnCheckpointIDs = [cpB]\\n- B pushes → both cpA + cpB pushed (provisional)\\n  - PrePush sets PushedDuringTurnRemote on both A and B\\n- B ends turn → finalizes cpB → pushes cpB' → remote updated\\n- A ends turn → finalizes cpA → pushes cpA' → remote updated\\n\\nEach session handles its own finalization and push independently. Pushes are idempotent (`pushBranchIfNeeded` checks local vs remote hash).\\n\\n## Known Limitation\\n\\nIn the concurrent multi-session edge case where session A has both pushed and unpushed checkpoints (A commits cpA1, B pushes, A commits cpA2, A ends turn), the turn-end push will push the entire `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch — including cpA2's metadata which was never explicitly pushed by the user.\\n\\nThis can result in unattached checkpoints in the remote corpus if the corresponding code commit (A2) is never pushed. This scenario requires:\\n- Concurrent ACTIVE sessions in the same worktree\\n- Specific commit/push interleaving\\n\\nThis is rare and can be addressed with future checkpoint GC (pruning checkpoints that don't match any commit's `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer).\\n\\n## Transparency\\n\\n- Stderr message when pushing on turn-end: `[entire] Pushing finalized checkpoint transcripts to <remote>...`\\n- Gated by the same `push_sessions` setting that controls PrePush behavior\\n- No silent pushes — users always see when transcripts go to remote\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go` — add `PushedDuringTurnRemote` field\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_push.go` — set flag on ACTIVE sessions after successful push\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — push in `HandleTurnEnd` when flag is set\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — clear flag in `InitializeSession`\\n- Tests for each change\\n\",\"structuredPatch\":[],\"originalFile\":null},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"7a7b70b3-6544-4ceb-9ddb-205e6a13ab85\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"6fc71980-4a82-47cc-9df4-8bb34e4043c9\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/4\",\"sessionId\":\"26fd10e5-9929-4364-b5e7-540290e8931b\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/stop-hook-updates-remote-checkpoints\",\"slug\":\"composed-humming-rocket\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01M1V5SeLjNQHEYcdLDrDR8w\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now let me invoke the writing-plans skill to create the implementation plan.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1767,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":69274,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1767},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYmSaoXHwM565yGksL6mF\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"efca9e63-d8a1-4624-80c6-6e6a7f0cbd5b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T07:35:52.434Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"efca9e63-d8a1-4624-80c6-6e6a7f0cbd5b\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/4\",\"sessionId\":\"26fd10e5-9929-4364-b5e7-540290e8931b\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/stop-hook-updates-remote-checkpoints\",\"slug\":\"composed-humming-rocket\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01M1V5SeLjNQHEYcdLDrDR8w\",\"ty