"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Js4p44nBpm4JUGofdnRmuM\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Turn-End Checkpoint Push\\n     2→\\n     3→## Problem\\n     4→\\n     5→After an agent commits and pushes during a turn, the remote checkpoint on `entire/checkpoints/v1` contains a provisional transcript (whatever was available at commit time). When the turn ends, `HandleTurnEnd` finalizes the transcript with the complete prompt-to-stop conversation — but this update stays local. The remote checkpoint is now stale.\\n     6→\\n     7→This creates three issues:\\n     8→\\n     9→1. **Stale remote data** — the web UI shows the provisional transcript, missing the trailing conversation after the last commit.\\n    10→2. **Misattribution on next commit** — if the user commits again later, the trailing conversation gets condensed into the *next* checkpoint. It semantically belongs to the previous one.\\n    11→3. **Data loss if user never returns** — if the session is never revisited, the trailing conversation exists only on the local shadow branch and is never pushed.\\n    12→\\n    13→## Current Flow\\n    14→\\n    15→```\\n    16→TurnStart → ACTIVE\\n    17→Agent makes changes\\n    18→Agent commits → PostCommit condenses to entire/checkpoints/v1 (local)\\n    19→Agent pushes  → PrePush pushes entire/checkpoints/v1 (remote has provisional transcript)\\n    20→Agent continues working...\\n    21→TurnEnd → IDLE\\n    22→  └─ SaveStep writes trailing conversation to shadow branch\\n    23→  └─ HandleTurnEnd finalizes transcript on entire/checkpoints/v1 (LOCAL ONLY)\\n    24→  └─ Remote is now behind ← THE GAP\\n    25→```\\n    26→\\n    27→## Design\\n    28→\\n    29→### Core Idea\\n    30→\\n    31→Track whether a push happened during the current turn. If it did, push the finalized checkpoints on turn-end so the remote stays consistent.\\n    32→\\n    33→### Session State Addition\\n    34→\\n    35→Add a new field to `session.State`:\\n    36→\\n    37→```go\\n    38→// PushedDuringTurnRemote is set by PrePush when checkpoints are pushed\\n    39→// while the session is ACTIVE with TurnCheckpointIDs. Stores the remote\\n    40→// name so turn-end can push the finalized transcript to the same remote.\\n    41→// Empty string means no push happened during this turn.\\n    42→PushedDuringTurnRemote string `json:\\\"pushed_during_turn_remote,omitempty\\\"`\\n    43→```\\n    44→\\n    45→### PrePush Changes\\n    46→\\n    47→After successfully pushing `entire/checkpoints/v1`, iterate all ACTIVE sessions that have non-empty `TurnCheckpointIDs` and set `PushedDuringTurnRemote = remote` on each.\\n    48→\\n    49→This records: \\\"your provisional checkpoint is now visible remotely — when you finalize it, push the update.\\\"\\n    50→\\n    51→### HandleTurnEnd Changes\\n    52→\\n    53→After `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints` succeeds:\\n    54→\\n    55→1. Check if `PushedDuringTurnRemote` is non-empty\\n    56→2. Verify `push_sessions` setting is not disabled (belt and suspenders)\\n    57→3. Print `[entire] Pushing finalized checkpoint transcripts to <remote>...` to stderr\\n    58→4. Call `pushBranchIfNeeded(ctx, remote, paths.MetadataBranchName)`\\n    59→5. Push trails branch if applicable\\n    60→6. Clear `PushedDuringTurnRemote`\\n    61→\\n    62→### InitializeSession Changes\\n    63→\\n    64→Clear `PushedDuringTurnRemote` on new turn start (alongside existing `TurnCheckpointIDs` clearing).\\n    65→\\n    66→### Proposed Flow (After)\\n    67→\\n    68→```\\n    69→TurnStart → ACTIVE\\n    70→Agent makes changes\\n    71→Agent commits → PostCommit condenses to entire/checkpoints/v1 (local)\\n    72→Agent pushes  → PrePush pushes entire/checkpoints/v1 (remote has provisional)\\n    73→             → PrePush sets PushedDuringTurnRemote on ACTIVE sessions with TurnCheckpointIDs\\n    74→Agent continues working...\\n    75→TurnEnd → IDLE\\n    76→  └─ SaveStep writes trailing conversation to shadow branch\\n    77→  └─ HandleTurnEnd finalizes transcript on entire/checkpoints/v1 (local)\\n    78→  └─ HandleTurnEnd sees PushedDuringTurnRemote, pushes entire/checkpoints/v1 ← NEW\\n    79→  └─ Remote now has finalized transcript ✓\\n    80→```\\n    81→\\n    82→## Multi-Session Scenarios\\n    83→\\n    84→### Scenario 1: IDLE + two ACTIVE sessions\\n    85→\\n    86→- IDLE session A contributed a checkpoint on a prior turn\\n    87→- ACTIVE session B is doing research (no commits)\\n    88→- ACTIVE session C commits and pushes → A+C checkpoints pushed\\n    89→  - PrePush sets `PushedDuringTurnRemote` on C (ACTIVE with TurnCheckpointIDs)\\n    90→  - B has no TurnCheckpointIDs, so not flagged\\n    91→- C ends turn → finalizes C's transcript → pushes → remote up to date\\n    92→\\n    93→### Scenario 2: Two ACTIVE sessions both committing\\n    94→\\n    95→- A commits → A.TurnCheckpointIDs = [cpA]\\n    96→- B commits → B.TurnCheckpointIDs = [cpB]\\n    97→- B pushes → both cpA + cpB pushed (provisional)\\n    98→  - PrePush sets PushedDuringTurnRemote on both A and B\\n    99→- B ends turn → finalizes cpB → pushes cpB' → remote updated\\n   100→- A ends turn → finalizes cpA → pushes cpA' → remote updated\\n   101→\\n   102→Each session handles its own finalization and push independently. Pushes are idempotent (`pushBranchIfNeeded` checks local vs remote hash).\\n   103→\\n   104→## Known Limitation\\n   105→\\n   106→In the concurrent multi-session edge case where session A has both pushed and unpushed checkpoints (A commits cpA1, B pushes, A commits cpA2, A ends turn), the turn-end push will push the entire `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch — including cpA2's metadata which was never explicitly pushed by the user.\\n   107→\\n   108→This can result in unattached checkpoints in the remote corpus if the corresponding code commit (A2) is never pushed. This scenario requires:\\n   109→- Concurrent ACTIVE sessions in the same worktree\\n   110→- Specific commit/push interleaving\\n   111→\\n   112→This is rare and can be addressed with future checkpoint GC (pruning checkpoints that don't match any commit's `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer).\\n   113→\\n   114→## Transparency\\n   115→\\n   116→- Stderr message when pushing on turn-end: `[entire] Pushing finalized checkpoint transcripts to <remote>...`\\n   117→- Gated by the same `push_sessions` setting that controls PrePush behavior\\n   118→- No silent pushes — users always see when transcripts go to remote\\n   119→\\n   120→## Files to Modify\\n   121→\\n   122→- `cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go` — add `PushedDuringTurnRemote` field\\n   123→- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_push.go` — set flag on ACTIVE sessions after successful push\\n   124→- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — push in `HandleTurnEnd` when flag is set\\n   125→- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — clear flag in `InitializeSession`\\n   126→- Tests for each change\\n   127→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"83cff6ed-0c91-4a57-90c6-7d54e820b15d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T07:36:37.524Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/4/docs/plans/2026-03-06-turn-end-checkpoint-push-design.md\",\"content\":\"# Turn-End Checkpoint Push\\n\\n## Problem\\n\\nAfter an agent commits and pushes during a turn, the remote checkpoint on `entire/checkpoints/v1` contains a provisional transcript (whatever was available at commit time). When the turn ends, `HandleTurnEnd` finalizes the transcript with the complete prompt-to-stop conversation — but this update stays local. The remote checkpoint is now stale.\\n\\nThis creates three issues:\\n\\n1. **Stale remote data** — the web UI shows the provisional transcript, missing the trailing conversation after the last commit.\\n2. **Misattribution on next commit** — if the user commits again later, the trailing conversation gets condensed into the *next* checkpoint. It semantically belongs to the previous one.\\n3. **Data loss if user never returns** — if the session is never revisited, the trailing conversation exists only on the local shadow branch and is never pushed.\\n\\n## Current Flow\\n\\n```\\nTurnStart → ACTIVE\\nAgent makes changes\\nAgent commits → PostCommit condenses to entire/checkpoints/v1 (local)\\nAgent pushes  → PrePush pushes entire/checkpoints/v1 (remote has provisional transcript)\\nAgent continues working...\\nTurnEnd → IDLE\\n  └─ SaveStep writes trailing conversation to shadow branch\\n  └─ HandleTurnEnd finalizes transcript on entire/checkpoints/v1 (LOCAL ONLY)\\n  └─ Remote is now behind ← THE GAP\\n```\\n\\n## Design\\n\\n### Core Idea\\n\\nTrack whether a push happened during the current turn. If it did, push the finalized checkpoints on turn-end so the remote stays consistent.\\n\\n### Session State Addition\\n\\nAdd a new field to `session.State`:\\n\\n```go\\n// PushedDuringTurnRemote is set by PrePush when checkpoints are pushed\\n// while the session is ACTIVE with TurnCheckpointIDs. Stores the remote\\n// name so turn-end can push the finalized transcript to the same remote.\\n// Empty string means no push happened during this turn.\\nPushedDuringTurnRemote string `json:\\\"pushed_during_turn_remote,omitempty\\\"`\\n```\\n\\n### PrePush Changes\\n\\nAfter successfully pushing `entire/checkpoints/v1`, iterate all ACTIVE sessions that have non-empty `TurnCheckpointIDs` and set `PushedDuringTurnRemote = remote` on each.\\n\\nThis records: \\\"your provisional checkpoint is now visible remotely — when you finalize it, push the update.\\\"\\n\\n### HandleTurnEnd Changes\\n\\nAfter `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints` succeeds:\\n\\n1. Check if `PushedDuringTurnRemote` is non-empty\\n2. Verify `push_sessions` setting is not disabled (belt and suspenders)\\n3. Print `[entire] Pushing finalized checkpoint transcripts to <remote>...` to stderr\\n4. Call `pushBranchIfNeeded(ctx, remote, paths.MetadataBranchName)`\\n5. Push trails branch if applicable\\n6. Clear `PushedDuringTurnRemote`\\n\\n### InitializeSession Changes\\n\\nClear `PushedDuringTurnRemote` on new turn start (alongside existing `TurnCheckpointIDs` clearing).\\n\\n### Proposed Flow (After)\\n\\n```\\nTurnStart → ACTIVE\\nAgent makes changes\\nAgent commits → PostCommit condenses to entire/checkpoints/v1 (local)\\nAgent pushes  → PrePush pushes entire/checkpoints/v1 (remote has provisional)\\n             → PrePush sets PushedDuringTurnRemote on ACTIVE sessions with TurnCheckpointIDs\\nAgent continues working...\\nTurnEnd → IDLE\\n  └─ SaveStep writes trailing conversation to shadow branch\\n  └─ HandleTurnEnd finalizes transcript on entire/checkpoints/v1 (local)\\n  └─ HandleTurnEnd sees PushedDuringTurnRemote, pushes entire/checkpoints/v1 ← NEW\\n  └─ Remote now has finalized transcript ✓\\n```\\n\\n## Multi-Session Scenarios\\n\\n### Scenario 1: IDLE + two ACTIVE sessions\\n\\n- IDLE session A contributed a checkpoint on a prior turn\\n- ACTIVE session B is doing research (no commits)\\n- ACTIVE session C commits and pushes → A+C checkpoints pushed\\n  - PrePush sets `PushedDuringTurnRemote` on C (ACTIVE with TurnCheckpointIDs)\\n  - B has no TurnCheckpointIDs, so not flagged\\n- C ends turn → finalizes C's transcript → pushes → remote up to date\\n\\n### Scenario 2: Two ACTIVE sessions both committing\\n\\n- A commits → A.TurnCheckpointIDs = [cpA]\\n- B commits → B.TurnCheckpointIDs = [cpB]\\n- B pushes → both cpA + cpB pushed (provisional)\\n  - PrePush sets PushedDuringTurnRemote on both A and B\\n- B ends turn → finalizes cpB → pushes cpB' → remote updated\\n- A ends turn → finalizes cpA → pushes cpA' → remote updated\\n\\nEach session handles its own finalization and push independently. Pushes are idempotent (`pushBranchIfNeeded` checks local vs remote hash).\\n\\n## Known Limitation\\n\\nIn the concurrent multi-session edge case where session A has both pushed and unpushed checkpoints (A commits cpA1, B pushes, A commits cpA2, A ends turn), the turn-end push will push the entire `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch — including cpA2's metadata which was never explicitly pushed by the user.\\n\\nThis can result in unattached checkpoints in the remote corpus if the corresponding code commit (A2) is never pushed. This scenario requires:\\n- Concurrent ACTIVE sessions in the same worktree\\n- Specific commit/push interleaving\\n\\nThis is rare and can be addressed with future checkpoint GC (pruning checkpoints that don't match any commit's `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer).\\n\\n## Transparency\\n\\n- Stderr message when pushing on turn-end: `[entire] Pushing finalized checkpoint transcripts to <remote>...`\\n- Gated by the same `push_sessions` setting that controls PrePush behavior\\n- No silent pushes — users always see when transcripts go to remote\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go` — add `PushedDuringTurnRemote` field\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_push.go` — set flag on ACTIVE sessions after successful push\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — push in `HandleTurnEnd` when flag is set\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — clear flag in `InitializeSession`\\n- Tests for each change\\n\",\"numLines\":127,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":127}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"ae710821-9cd8-4e29-8cfc-fc9b72c4486a\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"83cff6ed-0c91-4a57-90c6-7d54e820b15d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/4\",\"sessionId\":\"26fd10e5-9929-4364-b5e7-540290e8931b\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/stop-hook-updates-remote-checkpoints\",\"slug\":\"composed-humming-rocket\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01WHPiX4iJQvM1n6Qfp8WvrV\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now let me write the implementation plan.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2157,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":91170,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":2157},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYmSeNfgPyzgieKxFFy6i\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"d5f6cba7-9fb0-43a7-b49d-567bac64cb80\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T07:36:40.451Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d5f6cba7-9fb0-43a7-b49d-567bac64cb80\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/4\",\"sessionId\":\"26fd10e5-9929-4364-b5e7-540290e8931b\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/stop-hook-updates-remote-checkpoints\",\"slug\":\"composed-humming-rocket\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01WHPiX4iJQvM1n6Qfp8WvrV\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_013skC7vbaxUqTae56xeZDfH\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/4/docs/plans/2026-03-06-turn-end-checkpoint-push.md\",\"content\":\"# Turn-End Checkpoint Push — Implementation Plan\\n\\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\\n\\n**Goal:** After an agent commits and pushes during a turn, ensure the finalized transcript (updated at turn-end) is also pushed to remote so the remote checkpoint stays consistent.\\n\\n**Architecture:** Add a `PushedDuringTurnRemote` field to session state. PrePush sets it on ACTIVE sessions with `TurnCheckpointIDs` after a successful checkpoint push. `HandleTurnEnd` checks this flag and pushes `entire/checkpoints/v1` after finalizing transcripts. Cleared on next turn start.\\n\\n**Tech Stack:** Go, go-git, git CLI (for push operations)\\n\\n**Design doc:** `docs/plans/2026-03-06-turn-end-checkpoint-push-design.md`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 1: Add `PushedDuringTurnRemote` field to session state\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/ent