led unconditionally even when `pushSessionsBranchCommon` returned early due to push being disabled. Fixed by adding `if !isPushSessionsDisabled(ctx)` guard in `PrePush` before calling `markActiveSessionsPushed`.\\n     - **Trails push scope creep**: `pushFinalizedCheckpointsIfNeeded` pushed both checkpoints and trails, but trails have a different lifecycle. User confirmed: \\\"trails lives on a different lifecycle, let's not complicate it right now\\\". Removed the `PushTrailsBranch` call.\\n\\n5. Problem Solving:\\n   - **Core problem**: Remote checkpoint staleness after turn-end transcript finalization. Solved by tracking push state per-session and re-pushing on turn-end.\\n   - **User intent preservation**: Discussed and rejected auto-pushing on every turn-end. Only push when user already pushed during the turn (tracked via `PushedDuringTurnRemote`).\\n   - **Remote discovery**: PrePush gets remote from git hook args. Solved by storing remote name (not just boolean) in session state.\\n   - **Multi-session edge cases**: Extensively analyzed concurrent sessions. Accepted known limitation where branch-level push granularity can push unattached checkpoints in rare concurrent scenarios.\\n   - **ACTIVE_COMMITTED state**: User mentioned they previously tried this approach and it got messy. Avoided by using the simpler `PushedDuringTurnRemote` flag approach.\\n\\n6. All user messages:\\n   - \\\"we currently have a gap in the visible remote checkpoints: start turn, agent makes changes, agent commits and pushes (checkpoints sync'd), agent ends turn (trailing conversation is added to checkpoint - please confirm this), remote checkpoint state is 'behind'. how might we remedy this situation?\\\"\\n   - \\\"both really, the user may never return to that session (note: also check the endSession flow in that case). the web UI has stale data and the trailing conversation _really_ belongs to the checkpoint that has just gone, not the next checkpoint - which is what I assume would happen in the next postcommit?\\\"\\n   - \\\"it wouldn't be ENDED, just IDLE\\\"\\n   - \\\"yes, this should only happen if there's been a commit within the same turn. we previously had an ACTIVE_COMMITTED state to track this but it got very messy. We also need to keep the multi-session semantics in mind.\\\"\\n   - \\\"I _thought_ we had already added the checkpoint amendments 😅 that's why I asked specifically 🤣 just reading through the code now... we don't know for sure that we've pushed in-turn - correct? so we could get to turn end and: 1. commits happened a) push happened - we are behind b) no push happened - we are 'ok' 2. no commits happened - we are 'ok'. with the remote discovery - how does pre-push resolve the remote?\\\"\\n   - \\\"I think we need to respect the user intention, they may not _want_ to push the checkpoints yet - there might be different reasons for this. 2. is there a way to do something similar to `git branch -vv`...\\\"\\n   - \\\"won't an unrelated remote update also trigger in Option A?\\\"\\n   - \\\"let's think about this... [detailed multi-session scenarios with A, B, C sessions]... does it make sense for each session to handle its own commit amendments and pushes on end-turn? so yes to updating push state on all ACTIVE sessions with TurnCheckpointIDs?\\\"\\n   - \\\"🤯 in that edge case... if A1 and A2 are the two code-side commits... A1+cpA1 is pushed (by B's push), but A2+cpA2 is not...and at turn end if we are trying to maintain the checkpoint integrity as well as _intent_, then we should only commit cpA1' and push it...while leaving A2+cpA2' local? this is diabolical\\\"\\n   - \\\"B leaves us where we are in that complex case but might be okay? but pragmatically I think A is okay, we just need to be pretty transparent about when people's transcripts are going up to the cloud 😅\\\"\\n   - \\\"yep, let's do it\\\"\\n   - \\\"proceed, subagents please\\\"\\n   - \\\"why gitutil vs the existing gitops package?\\\"\\n   - \\\"let's clear out anything that's not related to our work please\\\"\\n   - \\\"commit\\\"\\n   - \\\"push and draft pr\\\"\\n   - \\\"/entire-internal:github-pr-review\\\" (invoked PR review skill)\\n   - \\\"yes, we shouldn't mark it as pushed if it didn't happen. trails lives on a different lifecycle, let's not complicate it right now\\\"\\n\\n7. Pending Tasks:\\n   - No explicitly pending tasks. All 7 implementation tasks completed. PR review feedback addressed. PR is in draft state at https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/636\\n   - Design docs (`docs/plans/2026-03-06-turn-end-checkpoint-push-design.md` and `docs/plans/2026-03-06-turn-end-checkpoint-push.md`) are in the worktree but not committed.\\n\\n8. Current Work:\\n   The most recent work was addressing PR review feedback on draft PR #636. Three automated review comments (from Cursor and Copilot) were addressed in commit d2f143f6:\\n   1. Added `!isPushSessionsDisabled(ctx)` guard before `markActiveSessionsPushed` in PrePush\\n   2. Removed `PushTrailsBranch` call from `pushFinalizedCheckpointsIfNeeded`\\n   \\n   The fix was committed, pushed, and replies posted to all three review threads. The PR is at https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/636 in draft state.\\n\\n9. Optional Next Step:\\n   No explicit next step was requested. The PR is in draft and all review feedback has been addressed. The user may want to mark the PR as ready for review, or there may be additional human review pending. The design docs in `docs/plans/` are uncommitted but were not explicitly requested to be committed.\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before compaction (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alex/.claude/projects/-Users-alex-workspace-cli--worktrees-4/26fd10e5-9929-4364-b5e7-540290e8931b.jsonl\"},\"isVisibleInTranscriptOnly\":true,\"isCompactSummary\":true,\"uuid\":\"92b2eeb5-de75-43e6-889b-bf2e51353fe0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T10:59:56.394Z\"}\n{\"