\\nfunc (s *RepoState) RunPrompt(t *testing.T, ctx context.Context, prompt string, opts ...agents.Option) (agents.Output, error)\\n```\\n\\nThe flow is:\\n- `ForEachAgent()` wrapper runs the test in parallel for each registered agent (claude-code, gemini, opencode, cursor, vogon)\\n- `SetupRepo()` creates a fresh git repo, seeds with initial commit, runs `entire enable` for that agent\\n- `RunPrompt()` executes the agent's CLI in the test repo directory\\n- Output is logged to `console.log` in the artifacts directory\\n- On transient API errors, the scenario automatically restarts with a fresh repo (up to 3 attempts)\\n\\n### 2. **How Git Hooks Fire in E2E Tests**\\n\\nHooks are fired **by the agent binary itself**, not installed by the CLI:\\n\\n- **Real agents** (Claude Code, Gemini, OpenCode): Fire hooks via their native mechanisms when they run git commands\\n- **Vogon agent** (canary/deterministic): Explicitly calls `entire hooks vogon <verb>` after each action:\\n  - `session-start` (at agent startup)\\n  - `user-prompt-submit` (when user submits prompt)\\n  - `stop` (when agent finishes turn)\\n  - `session-end` (at agent shutdown)\\n\\nThe vogon agent also handles git operations directly (create/modify/delete files, commit) and invokes `git commit` which triggers the CLI's git hooks (prepare-commit-msg, post-commit, pre-push).\\n\\n### 3. **Vogon Agent Push Capabilities**\\n\\n**Current state: Vogon CANNOT simulate `git push`**\\n\\nVogon's `executeActions()` only handles:\\n- `\\\"create\\\"` - creates files\\n- `\\\"modify\\\"` - appends content to files\\n- `\\\"delete\\\"` - deletes files\\n- `\\\"commit\\\"` - runs `git add` + `git commit`\\n\\nThere is **no `\\\"push\\\"` action** in the prompt parser. The regex patterns (`createFileRe`, `modifyFileRe`, `deleteFileRe`, `commitRe`) don't match push instructions.\\n\\n**Gap:** To test push E2E scenarios, we need to either:\\n1. Add push support to the vogon agent (parse \\\"push to origin\\\" or similar 